textAfterTable: Notes: Giants are 4-1 for the first time since 1993. They finished at 11-5 in Dan Reeves' first season. The last five times the Giants won at Texas Stadium since 1989, they made the playoffs. Giants are now 13-3 in games before the bye week. Giants have won all 5 coin tosses this season. This was Tiki Barber's fourth 100-yard game this season. Tiki Barber's fourth-quarter touchdown was the first on the ground allowed by the Cowboys in 28 quarters. This was Jeremy Shockey's second touchdown of the season, and the sixth of his career. Amani Toomer caught a pass in his 88th consecutive game. Kicker Steve Christie was 4-for-4 after a three-miss performance the previous week. WR Tim Carter left the game with a hip injury in the first half and did not return. WR David Tyree took his place. Bill Parcells, until this game, had won four straight games coming off a bye week. Vinny Testaverde's second-quarter touchdown pass to WR Keyshawn Johnson was the 255th of his career, moving him into a tie with Sonny Jurgensen for 9th place on the NFL's all-time list.
